>cofin</i>, <i>coffin</i>, Old French <i>cof(f)in</i> (from Late Latin <i>cophinus</i>, Greek <i>kophinos</i>) ‘container, basket; coffer, chest (for keeping treasures, documents, armour, etc.)’. Early bearers of this as a hereditary surname were of knightly rank. Old French <i>cofin</i> was synonymous with <i>coffer</i>, and it may be that <i>Cofin</i> was used to denote a keeper of the (royal) coffer, attested in Anglo-Latin <i>cofferarius</i>. Compare   Coffer  . The modern English word <i>coffin</i> is a specialized development of this term, not attested until the 16th century.","History: Tristram Coffin came from Brixham, Devon, to Haverhill, MA, before 1647. An important line of his descendants is associated with Nantucket and Martha's Vineyard."],"variants":[{"name":"Coffer","meanings":["English: metonymic occupational name from Middle English <i>cofre</i>, <i>coffre</i>, <i>coffer</i> ‘box, chest’ (from Old French <i>cof(f)rehere</i>), used to denote a box or coffer maker (Old French <i>coffrier</i>), perhaps also for a treasurer.","Probably also an Americanized form of German   Kaufer   or <b>Kauffer</b>."]},{"name":"Coffing","meanings":["English: variant of   Coffin  ."]}]},{"name":"of","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Sung, Jung, Yong, Chang, Kwang, Sang, Dong, Hyun, Jae, Jin, Kyung, Jong, Chong, Chung, Byung, Jeong, Pyong, Myong, Hak, Jin Hwan, Sook, Yeong, Choon.","Korean: variant of   O  .","Japanese: variant of <b>Ō</b> (see   O  )."],"variants":[{"name":"O","meanings":["(1997: 122;2010: NA)","Some characteristic forenames:  Chinese Young, Bo Young, Chae, Chong Hwan, Dong Kun, Ho, Hwan, Hyun, Jong, Jung, Ki Soon, Kwang.  Korean Min, Chong, Chol, Jung Ho, Myong, Sa, Sung Kyun.","Korean (오; Chinese character: 吳): historically, there were two Chinese characters for the O surname, but by the late Koryŏ period (14th century  AD ), one of them had disappeared. Some records indicate that there are as many as 210 different clans for the remaining character, but only sixteen can be positively documented. All sixteen of these clans originate from the same ancestor, O Ch’ŏm (吳 瞻), who migrated to Korea from China during the reign of Shilla's King Chijŭng (500–514  AD ). <i>O</i> is a common surname throughout Korea. Compare   Oh  ."]}]},{"name":"Beacombe","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Seacombe (Cheshire)."],"variants":[{"name":"Seacome","meanings":["English:  see  Seacombe  ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Coffin of Beacombe was born in 1060, in England, United Kingdom. He married nn nn in 1080, in England. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter."},"et":{"1060–":"1060–Surnud","1065–Female":"1065–Surnud","1092–Female":"1092–Surnud","1060–Male":"1060–Surnud","1080":"1080","1065":"1065","ABT 1092":"umbes 1092","1060":"1060","1092":"1092","England":"England","Beacombe,Devon,England":"Devon, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","England, United Kingdom":"Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1060–":"1060–Kuollut","1065–Female":"1065–Kuollut","1092–Female":"1092–Kuollut","1060–Male":"1060–Kuollut","1080":"1080","1065":"1065","ABT 1092":"noin 1092","1060":"1060","1092":"1092","England":"England","Beacombe,Devon,England":"Devon, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","England, United Kingdom":"Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1060–":"1060–Décédé","1065–Female":"1065–Décédée","1092–Female":"1092–Décédée","1060–Male":"1060–Décédé","1080":"1080","1065":"1065","ABT 1092":"environ 1092","1060":"1060","1092":"1092","England":"Angleterre","Beacombe,Devon,England":"Devon, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","England, United Kingdom":"Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Coffin of Beacombe est né en 1060, à Angleterre, Royaume-Uni. Il a épousé nn nn en 1080, à Angleterre. Ils ont eu au moins 1 fille."},"de":